   "source": [
    "**8.1 Formulation of the null and alternative hypotheses.  \n",
    "Hypothesis 1: number of orders per user:  \n",
    "H0 (null hypothesis): the average number of orders per user of the mobile application is not greater than that of desktop users.  \n",
    "H1 (alternative): the average number of orders per user of the mobile application is higher than that of desktop users.**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 72,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Let's prepare the data for hypotheses. We count the number of orders per user for each device category\n",
    "orders_per_user = df_autumn.groupby(['user_id','device_type_canonical'])['order_id'].count().reset_index()\n",
    "# We split into mobile and desktop\n",
    "mobile_orders = orders_per_user[orders_per_user['device_type_canonical'] == 'mobile']['order_id']\n",
    "desktop_orders = orders_per_user[orders_per_user['device_type_canonical'] == 'desktop']['order_id']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 73,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
